The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 AIDS helpline

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Hyderabad, Dec. 29: Satyam Foundation, the corporate social responsibility arm of software developer Satyam Computer Services, and the government of Andhra Pradesh are planning a helpline focusing on assistance to the HIV-affected. 

 The foundation and the states health authorities today signed a memorandum of understanding to set up a call centre and the helpline, Hello Doctor 1056, at the cost of Rs 10 crore in a private-public partnership. 

 Satyam Foundation will set up a 50-seat call centre with a capacity to take 6,000 calls a day. The application software will be provided by Satyam, said Dr Balaji Utla, the director of Satyam Foundation.

 Satyam will also provide training to the personnel to handle the call centre. 

 The focus of the helpline will be to contain the spread of HIV and AIDS in Andhra, the state with the highest number of such cases. 




